[Patient] What kind of exercise do you recommend for managing my heart failure?
[Educator] Walking or swimming are great options to start with, and help improve your heart health.
[Patient] I'm not sure where to find a safe place to walk or swim in my neighborhood.
[Educator] Look for local community centers or parks that offer walking paths or swimming pools.
[Patient] Are there any specific exercises I should avoid due to my heart condition?
[Educator] Avoid high-intensity activities like sprinting or heavy weightlifting, and focus on low-impact exercises.
[Patient] How often should I exercise to see the benefits for my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of exercise most days of the week to improve your heart health.